                                <condition>A block in two pieces bearing bilingual inscriptions. There are two <q>intact</q> (Macalister 1945, 444) ogham inscriptions and an incomplete Latin inscription which is <q>only slightly deteriorated</q> (Okasha 1993, 150).</condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout>The ogham inscriptions occupy the two front angles of the stone. Both ogham inscriptions read vertically downwards. However, Macalister noted that the left-hand inscription is a correction of the ogham on the right, <q>made after the cutter had discovered that he had misplaced the side-scores</q> (1945, 444). Between the ogham inscriptions, a Latin inscription is written in one line, reading vertically downwards and facing to the left, on the face of the stone.</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>The Latin inscription is written without the assistance of <q>framing-lines or panels</q> (Okasha 1993, 150). <height min="6" max="11" unit="cm">The letters of the Latin inscription measure between 6 to 11 cm in height.</height>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
